  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "`MirrorPolicyImpl::shouldMirror` will override a default runtime fraction of 0, and instead mirror 100% of the time.\r\n https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/6ca8500b39568049647f4f40a599b8f8bd2afc3d/source/extensions/filters/network/redis_proxy/router_impl.cc#L17-L32\r\n\r\nThis is at odds with documentation:\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/6ca8500b39568049647f4f40a599b8f8bd2afc3d/api/envoy/api/v2/route/route.proto#L612-L617\r\n\r\n```\r\n    // If not specified, all requests to the target cluster will be mirrored. If\r\n    // specified, Envoy will lookup the runtime key to get the % of requests to\r\n    // mirror. Valid values are from 0 to 10000, allowing for increments of\r\n    // 0.01% of requests to be mirrored. If the runtime key is specified in the\r\n    // configuration but not present in runtime, 0 is the default and thus 0% of\r\n    // requests will be mirrored.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd also inconsistent with the behavior of http router traffic mirroring:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/eff020170c6267e6c8dc235473f7fc85c5b1e07d/source/common/router/config_impl.cc#L180-L185",
